% show the fractions using a circle
Construct a circle with centre A and radius r=3 units
Mark a point on the object(circle) as B
Join AB
Create a slider b with min=2, max=100, increment=1
Create a slider a with min=1,max=b,increment=1
Sequence(Segment(A,Rotate(B,f^o,A)))
Sequence(Segment(A,Rotate(B,f^0,A))f,360^0/b,360,360/b)
Use the tool angle with given side from B to A
Angle=360^0a\b
Circular arec ABB'
Repeat step9,10 and 11 and change the colour.
End

https://www.geogebra.org/m/s7u6qq3n
